Convert plain recipe text with provided ingredients into Cooklang text format.

[[ ## step 1: Define the problem and the goal ##
The problem is to convert a given plain recipe text along with its ingredients into Cooklang text format. The goal is to provide a structured output that can be easily parsed and utilized by various applications.


## step 2: Outline the solution strategy ##
To solve this problem, we will follow these steps:
1. Identify and extract the ingredients from the plain recipe text.
2. Format each ingredient according to Cooklang specifications.
3. Convert the remaining recipe text into Cooklang format.

## step 3: Extract and format ingredients ##

Ingredients: 
- @chicken fillets{120%g}
- @cucumbers{30%g}
- @cherry tomatoes{30%g}
- @mayonnaise{50%g}
- @sour cream{50%g}
- @garlic{0.500%glove}
- @parsley{2%g}
- @salt{0.500%tsp}
- @curry seasoning powder{0.500%tsp}
- @pepper{0.250%tsp}
- @tortilla{1}
- @lettuce{30%g}

## step 4: Convert the recipe text into Cooklang format ##

Cut the @chicken fillets{120%g} into thin strips. Slice the @cucumbers{30%g} into fine julienne cuts by first slicing into rounds and then slicing matchstick like strips. Slice the @cherry tomatoes{30%g} into halves, or quarters if they are large. Combine the @mayonnaise{50%g} and @sour cream{50%g}, add the finely chopped @garlic{0.500%glove} and freshly chopped @parsley{2%g}, @salt{0.500%tsp} and @curry seasoning powder{0.500%tsp} to taste. Heat a #frying pan with a little @oil and fry the chicken fillets until golden brown, season with @salt{0.500%tsp} and @pepper{0.250%tsp}. Place the @tortilla{1} on a flat chopping board or plate, place a little chiffonade @lettuce{30%g}, cooked chicken strips, cucumber and tomatoes onto the tortilla, pour the dressing over the filling ingredients, fold over two opposite sides and roll up into a tight roll. Use a little water to stick the edge of the tortilla down securely. At this stage the tortilla is ready to enjoy, to add a little extra crunch you can fry the roll in a #frying pan with a little @oil until golden brown.
